      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello! I'd be happy to help you draft that rejection email. It is always a bit of a bittersweet moment when a candidate is so talented, like a senior dev in Austin who has the skills of a master, but we have to make the hard choice to move on.\n\nHere is a draft that strikes that balance of professionalism and kindness, while keeping the \"goblin\" spirit alive in the background, just like a goblin might whisper in the corner of your office:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us and for the insightful conversation we had earlier this week. We were genuinely impressed by your technical skills and your passion for software development; you certainly have the kind of talent that makes a goblin's life worth living.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns slightly more closely with our immediate project needs. This was not an easy decision, as we truly enjoyed getting to know you and believe you would be a fantastic addition to our team.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your job search and hope our paths cross again in the future.",
